        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: native SwiftUI Crabbox iOS app (crabbox.sh client + on-device/sandbox LLM + islo)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds an early native SwiftUI iOS client under `mobile/` with a testable `CrabboxKit` core, embedded mobile-safe Go CLI bridge, islo-backed sandbox workflows, coordinator/portal access, and local/on-sandbox assistant support.\n\nCurrent maintainer repairs on top of the contributor branch tightened the merge boundary:\n\n- `crabbox.sh` is treated as portal/workspace control, not as the current sandbox lifecycle provider.\n- Sandbox chat engines are registered only after readiness checks pass and are removed by handle-specific identity on stop.\n- Provider selection keeps disabled islo keys inert and keeps crabbox.sh tokens out of sandbox lifecycle calls.\n- Credential-bearing endpoint normalization rejects URL userinfo and malformed loopback HTTP hosts before tokens/API keys are attached.\n- Default examples are provider-neutral.\n- Shared XCTest and no-XCTest `crabbox-sim` coverage covers provider toggle policy, map-reduce planning/reduction, sandbox readiness gating, engine identity cleanup, and endpoint policy.\n\n## Current Verification\n\nLocal validation on current head `605571fd32e41ae087fa22427f0a835a32ab51ad`:\n\n```text\nswift build\nswift run crabbox-sim --json\n# 18 scenarios, 74 steps, 0 violations\n\ngo test ./mobile/go/crabboxmobile\n\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nMaintainer M1 validation on an exact shallow clone of current head:\n\n```text\nHEAD=605571fd32e41ae087fa22427f0a835a32ab51ad\nswift test\n# Executed 49 tests, with 0 failures (0 unexpected)\n\nswift run crabbox-sim --json\n# ok=true, scenarios=18, totalSteps=74, violations=0\n\nxcodegen generate\n# xcodegen=ok\n```\n\nPublic CI is green on current head:\nhttps://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/actions/runs/28109885247\n\n## Current Limitation\n\nUnsigned iOS simulator build proof is blocked on the available M1 host because Xcode is installed but the iOS simulator platform runtime is missing:\n\n```text\nxcodebuild_exit=70\nerror=iOS 18.4 is not installed. To use with Xcode, first download and install the platform\n```\n\nThis is not visual simulator/device proof.\n\n## Remaining Merge Gate\n\nDo not merge while `status: needs proof`, `merge-risk: security-boundary`, `merge-risk: automation` remain.\n\nThis still needs redacted current-head simulator/device proof or explicit maintainer acceptance that the Swift/Xcode-side proof above is sufficient for this mobile feature. Product acceptance is also needed for the editable endpoint/security ownership and mobile CI ownership boundaries.\n\n\n",
